1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,040
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:04,040 --> 00:00:05,040
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:06,160
My name is Catherine.
我是Catherine。

4
00:00:06,160 --> 00:00:10,080
And as you know, we've had a series going about small talk in English.
如你们所知，我们一直在做一个关于英语闲聊的系列节目。

5
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:12,480
So today's lesson is a part of that series.
所以今天的课程是这个系列的一部分。

6
00:00:12,480 --> 00:00:13,480
That's right.
没错。

7
00:00:13,480 --> 00:00:18,080
Today we're going to listen to two friends, two girlfriends meeting and they haven't seen
今天我们要听两个朋友，两个闺蜜见面，她们已经很久没见了。

8
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:19,480
each other for a long time.
她们很久没见了。

9
00:00:19,480 --> 00:00:24,440
So we're just going to see how they quickly have a small conversation.
所以我们来看看她们如何快速地进行一次简短对话。

10
00:00:24,440 --> 00:00:30,680
Hey Michelle, is that you?
嘿，Michelle，是你吗？

11
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:34,120
Wow, Grace, long time no see.
哇，Grace，好久不见。

12
00:00:34,120 --> 00:00:35,120
Where have you been?
你去哪儿了？

13
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:40,920
Oh yeah, well, you see I got a promotion so I moved to the new Pudong office last September.
哦，是啊，嗯，你看我升职了，所以去年九月搬到了新的浦东办公室。

14
00:00:40,920 --> 00:00:41,920
You did?
真的吗？

15
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:42,920
Congratulations.
恭喜你。

16
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:44,200
Thanks a lot.
多谢。

17
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:46,600
So how are things with you, Michelle?
那你怎么样，Michelle？

18
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:50,240
Well, same old, same old, you know, nothing much has changed here.
嗯，老样子，老样子，你知道的，这里没什么变化。

19
00:00:50,240 --> 00:00:51,720
Are you still seeing Chris?
你还在和Chris交往吗？

20
00:00:51,720 --> 00:00:54,400
No, actually we split up last month.
不，实际上我们上个月分手了。

21
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:57,640
Oh dear, I'm sorry to hear that.
哦，天哪，听到这个我很难过。

22
00:00:57,640 --> 00:01:01,120
But I met a really cute guy last night at a networking party.
但昨晚我在一个社交派对上遇到了一个很可爱的男生。

23
00:01:01,120 --> 00:01:03,800
So well, let's just wait and see.
所以嘛，我们就等着瞧吧。

24
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:06,120
Good for you, Michelle.
真为你高兴，米歇尔。

25
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:09,280
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

26
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:15,240
So now let's take a look at some of the language on Language Takeaway.
现在让我们来看看“语言要点”部分的一些表达。

27
00:01:15,240 --> 00:01:17,640
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

28
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:21,760
So the first word we have here today, Marco, is the word promotion.
马可，今天我们第一个词是“升职”。

29
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:27,520
Grace says, well, you see, I got a promotion so I moved to the new Pudong office.
格蕾丝说，嗯，你看，我升职了，所以搬到了新的浦东办公室。

30
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:28,520
That's right.
没错。

31
00:01:28,520 --> 00:01:32,700
So she got a promotion and a promotion is work related.
所以她升职了，而升职是和工作相关的。

32
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:35,160
That means that you got a better position.
这意味着你得到了一个更好的职位。

33
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:36,160
That's right.
没错。

34
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:37,160
But you didn't change companies.
但你没有换公司。

35
00:01:37,160 --> 00:01:41,600
So in your company, you had a job and you did well in that job.
所以在你公司里，你有一个职位，而且你做得很好。

36
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:44,800
And so your boss gave you a better job in the company.
然后你的老板给了你公司里一个更好的工作。

37
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:46,120
And that's a promotion.
那就是升职。

38
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:47,120
That's right.
没错。

39
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:49,200
Okay, so she got a promotion.
好的，所以她升职了。

40
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:53,400
Grace, when they were talking about work and now they started talking about their personal
格蕾丝，他们刚才在聊工作，现在开始聊个人生活了。

41
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:59,320
life and Grace asked if Michelle is still seeing Chris.
生活与格蕾丝问米歇尔是否还在和克里斯交往。

42
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:04,640
Okay, so the verb here is to see someone, to be seeing someone.
好的，这里的动词是“see someone”或“be seeing someone”。

43
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:06,960
We're not actually talking about eyes and looking.
我们实际上不是在谈论用眼睛看东西。

44
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,520
We're talking about dating.
我们是在谈论约会。

45
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:09,520
That's right.
没错。

46
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:12,760
So if you're seeing Chris, it means you are dating Chris.
所以如果你在“seeing Chris”，意思就是你在和克里斯约会。

47
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:13,760
Okay.
好的。

48
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:17,720
So that's an interesting way of describing a relationship.
这是一种描述关系的很有趣的方式。

49
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:21,000
So you say, yeah, I'm sorry, I'm seeing someone.
所以你可以说，是的，抱歉，我正在和别人交往。

50
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,000
I can't date you.
我不能和你约会。

51
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,280
I'm seeing someone else.
我在和别人交往。

52
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:26,920
Or you could ask someone, are you seeing anyone right now?
或者你可以问别人，你现在有在约会吗？

53
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:27,920
That means are you dating anyone?
意思就是你在和任何人约会吗？

54
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:30,000
Do you have a boyfriend basically?
基本上就是你有男朋友吗？

55
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,000
Okay.
好的。

56
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,840
And sadly, no, they are not together anymore.
可惜的是，不，他们不再在一起了。

57
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:37,080
She says, actually, we split up last month.
她说，实际上，我们上个月分手了。

58
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:38,080
All right.
好的。

59
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,480
So this is another relationship term.
所以这是另一个关系术语。

60
00:02:39,480 --> 00:02:43,840
To split up means to break up or to stop dating.
“Split up”意思是分手或停止约会。

61
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:45,880
To stop seeing each other.
不再见面了。

62
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:50,960
So there are two ways of seeing it, as you said, to split up or to break up.
所以有两种说法，就像你说的，split up 或 break up。

63
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:51,960
That's right.
没错。

64
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:54,720
So unfortunately, they split up or unfortunately, they broke up.
所以不幸的是，他们 split up 了，或者不幸的是，他们 broke up 了。

65
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:57,240
They are no longer seeing each other.
他们不再见面了。

66
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,240
That's right.
没错。

67
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,240
Okay.
好的。

68
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:04,440
But she said she had some good news because she met a really cute guy at a networking
但她说她有个好消息，因为她在一次社交

69
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,440
party.
派对上遇到了一个非常可爱的男生。

70
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:06,440
What is networking?
什么是 networking？

71
00:03:06,440 --> 00:03:07,440
All right.
好的。

72
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:11,400
So networking is something that you do, especially in the business world.
所以 networking 是你做的事情，尤其是在商业领域。

73
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:15,720
You go to events, parties, happy hours, and you meet people.
你去参加活动、派对、欢乐时光，然后认识人。

74
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:20,680
You meet strangers and you talk about work and you try to meet as many people as you
你遇到陌生人，聊工作，并尽量认识尽可能多的人。

75
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:21,680
can.
尽可能多的人。

76
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:22,680
Okay.
好的。

77
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:26,760
So it's not really a social party to actually just go and meet random people.
所以这并不真的只是一个随便认识陌生人的社交派对。

78
00:03:26,760 --> 00:03:31,200
You're trying to meet people that will be interesting for your business or maybe to
你是想认识那些对你的业务有帮助的人，或者可能

79
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,200
get some other ideas.
获得一些其他想法。

80
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:33,720
It's for a business purpose.
这是为了商业目的。

81
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:34,720
That's right.
没错。

82
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:40,040
So perhaps in your town, you own a small business and your town has decided to have a chamber
所以，也许在你的镇上，你经营着一家小企业，而你的镇子决定举办一场商会

83
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:42,120
of commerce networking party.
社交聚会。

84
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:44,720
So you can meet other small business owners.
这样你就可以认识其他小企业主。

85
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:45,720
Okay.
好的。

86
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:46,720
Very good.
非常好。

87
00:03:46,720 --> 00:03:48,680
So that's what we have for language takeaway.
这就是我们语言要点部分的内容。

88
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:52,320
Let's go back and listen to our dialogue for the second time.
让我们回去再听一遍对话。

89
00:03:52,320 --> 00:03:55,600
Hey, Michelle.
嘿，米歇尔。

90
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:59,000
Is that you?
是你吗？

91
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,400
Wow, Grace.
哇，格蕾丝。

92
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,280
Long time no see.
好久不见。

93
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:03,280
Where have you been?
你去哪儿了？

94
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,280
Oh yeah.
哦，是啊。

95
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:09,080
Well, you see, I got a promotion so I moved to the new Pudong office last September.
嗯，你看，我升职了，所以去年九月搬到了新的浦东办公室。

96
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,080
You did?
真的吗？

97
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,080
Congratulations.
恭喜你。

98
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,360
Thanks a lot.
多谢。

99
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:14,680
So how are things with you, Michelle?
那你最近怎么样，米歇尔？

100
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:18,360
Well, same old, same old, you know, nothing much has changed here.
嗯，老样子，老样子，你知道，这里没什么变化。

101
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:19,880
Are you still seeing Chris?
你还在和克里斯交往吗？

102
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:22,600
No, actually we split up last month.
不，实际上我们上个月分手了。

103
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,600
Oh dear.
哦，天哪。

104
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:25,720
I'm sorry to hear that.
听到这个我很难过。

105
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:29,200
But I met a really cute guy last night at a networking party.
但我昨晚在一个社交派对上遇到了一个很可爱的家伙。

106
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:31,720
So well, let's just wait and see.
所以，嗯，我们只能等着瞧了。

107
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:38,800
Good for you, Michelle.
那挺好的，米歇尔。

108
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:39,800
All right.
好了。

109
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:46,920
Let's talk about these small, quick but very useful phrases for small talk on Fluency Builder.
让我们在流利度构建环节聊聊这些简短、快速但非常有用的闲聊短语。

110
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,280
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建。

111
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:53,560
So this first phrase is a phrase that you'll hear a lot when people greet each other but
所以第一个短语是人们在打招呼时经常听到的，但

112
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:56,400
perhaps friends who haven't seen each other in a very long time.
也许是那些很久没见的朋友之间用的。

113
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:59,560
We use this phrase, long time no see.
我们用这个短语：好久不见。

114
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:00,560
That's right.
没错。

115
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:04,480
Now, you look at it and it may seem like it's incorrect, right?
现在，你看它，可能觉得语法不对，对吧？

116
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:06,560
Because you're missing something.
因为少了点什么。

117
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:07,560
That's right.
没错。

118
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,560
Long time no see.
好久不见。

119
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:09,560
Who no see?
谁没见？

120
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,560
What long time?
什么好久？

121
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,560
That's right.
没错。

122
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:14,800
But this actually means I haven't seen you in a long time.
但这实际上意思是“我很久没见到你了”。

123
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:15,800
That's right.
没错。

124
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:18,160
So the phrase is long time no see.
所以这个短语就是“好久不见”。

125
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:20,320
Hey, Michelle, long time no see.
嘿，米歇尔，好久不见。

126
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,760
How are you?
你好吗？

127
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:23,080
That's the way that you use it.
这就是它的用法。

128
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:24,880
But just take it as a phrase.
但就把它当做一个短语来用。

129
00:05:24,880 --> 00:05:26,440
Don't try to analyze it too much.
别分析太多。

130
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:28,720
So hey, Marco, long time no see.
所以，嘿，马可，好久不见。

131
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:29,720
That's right.
没错。

132
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:30,720
Okay.
好的。

133
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:33,000
And well, they're talking and she's like, well, how are you?
嗯，他们聊着，她问：“嗯，你怎么样？”

134
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:36,040
And she says, well, you know, same old, same old.
然后她说：“嗯，你知道，老样子，老样子。”

135
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,040
All right.
好了。

136
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,040
This is another one.
这是另一个短语。

137
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:39,040
It doesn't look right.
看起来不太对。

138
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,040
It doesn't look wrong.
看起来也没错。

139
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:43,600
But we do say this and twice, same old, same old.
但我们确实这么说，而且说两遍：老样子，老样子。

140
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:46,000
And this means nothing has changed.
这意思是没什么变化。

141
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,640
There's nothing really new in my life.
我的生活里没什么新鲜事。

142
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:49,640
Right.
对。

143
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:51,160
The same old things in my life.
还是那些老一套。

144
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:53,040
Nothing really new or exciting.
没什么新鲜或激动人心的。

145
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,040
Same old.
老样子。

146
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:55,040
Exactly.
没错。

147
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,960
So I could say, hey, Marco, how's the job going?
所以我可以问：“嘿，马可，工作怎么样？”

148
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:58,440
You know, same old, same old.
“你知道，老样子，老样子。”

149
00:05:58,440 --> 00:05:59,440
All right.
好了。

150
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:00,800
So nothing has changed in his job.
所以他的工作没什么变化。

151
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,640
He has not gotten a promotion.
他没升职。

152
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:03,640
That's right.
没错。

153
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:09,000
So now, Michelle was again describing about the guy that she met at the networking party
现在，米歇尔又在描述她在社交派对上遇到的那个家伙，

154
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:12,600
and she said, well, let's just wait and see.
她说：“嗯，我们只能等着瞧了。”

155
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:16,000
It seems like an incomplete sentence because let's wait and see what.
这看起来像是个不完整的句子，因为“等着瞧”什么？

156
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,000
All right.
好了。

157
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,200
So let's wait and see what?
所以“等着瞧”什么？

158
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:19,200
That's the question, though.
但问题就在这儿。

159
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:20,640
You know, what are we waiting to see?
你知道，我们在等着看什么？

160
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:25,440
Well, she's basically saying we don't know how things will go, but we, you know, we'll
嗯，她基本上是说我们不知道事情会怎么发展，但，你知道，我们只能

161
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:29,960
have to wait for the future to come before we can make a decision or figure out what's
必须等待未来到来，才能做出决定或弄清楚发生了什么。

162
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:30,960
going on.
没错。

163
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:31,960
That's right.
对。

164
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:35,600
So, for example, Marco, we're at the office and I say, how is that report coming along?
所以，比如，马可，我们在办公室，我问你，那份报告进展如何？

165
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:38,120
Is it, you know, were the numbers good?
你知道，数字好吗？

166
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:41,800
And I can say, yeah, the numbers seemed all right, but we'll just wait and see.
我可以说，嗯，数字看起来还行，但我们会等着瞧。

167
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:46,440
Perhaps we don't have all the numbers yet, so we have to wait to get the rest of them.
也许我们还没有全部数字，所以得等拿到剩下的再说。

168
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:47,440
That's right.
对。

169
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:51,800
So you're just basically saying I don't know what will happen in the future.
所以你基本上是在说，我不知道未来会发生什么。

170
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:56,040
Let's just hope that it will be good and let's see what happens.
就希望一切顺利，看看会发生什么。

171
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,360
Let's just wait and see.
